name: Saks Fifth Avenue Neiman Marcus
summary: Hudson's Bay Company (HBC), the parent company of Saks Fifth Avenue, will acquire Neiman Marcus Group for $2.65 billion in a deal that will combine two iconic luxury department store chains. The acquisition will create a retail giant with over 400 stores in North America and Europe. Amazon, which has partnered with HBC in the past, will invest approximately $500 million in HBC as part of the transaction and receive four seats on HBC's board of directors. The deal is expected to close by the end of the year, subject to approval from regulators and Neiman Marcus shareholders.

name: Kevin Bacon
summary: Actor Kevin Bacon recently embarked on an unusual experiment, disguising himself as an ordinary person to experience life outside the spotlight. According to multiple news sources, Bacon found the experience challenging and declared, "This sucks." The experiment, which was part of a promotional stunt, required Bacon to blend into a crowd and navigate everyday situations without being recognized.
